Pre-Game Insights: Egypt face Congo DR on Sunday for a quarterfinal slot in the 2023 Africa Cup of Nations.
Egypt concluded their group stage campaign with a thrilling 2-2 draw with Cape Verde.
DR Congo qualified as runners-up in Group F.
The winner of this tie will face either Equatorial Guinea or Guinea in the quarterfinal.
This will be the ninth meeting between the two sides, with Egypt winning six and drawing two.
Egypt have made the final in five of their last six AFCON appearances.
Both sides drew all three games in the group stage.
Nine of Congo DR's last 10 international games have produced less than three goals.
Each of Egypt's last six internationals have featured goals in both halves.
Congo DR have won just one of their last 10 internationals (six draws).
Both sides are yet to win their first game in the competition.
